{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"22625489-6776-4d0b-8f53-4f3a41cb03e1","content":"","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01XnB5NuBCWtASHeRztrSSgF","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Reviewing project files"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01QbBVfqKSgSjCVpCtup8zDd","name":"view","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-a9b10efd837b47dba4a23eaf096db29b/TestProject.csproj"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"view the file at /tmp/sv-a9b10efd837b47dba4a23eaf096db29b/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"a2807946-5445-4627-b1e3-506599bd0780","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a breaking change when upgrading from MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0 to MSTest.Sdk/4.1.0, specifically related to test discovery with vstest.console. This is a knowledge question about MSTest SDK changes.\n\nLet me look at the files in the current directory to understand the context better, and also think about what I know about this change.\n\nKey change: Starting with MSTest.Sdk 3.8.0, the SDK introduced support for Microsoft.Testing.Platform (the new test runner). However, it still supported VSTest by default. In MSTest.Sdk 3.x, the default was to use VSTest, and you could opt-in to Microsoft.Testing.Platform.\n\n\nIn version 4.0 and later, the default runner switched to Microsoft.Testing.Platform, which means vstest.console can no longer discover tests since the project no longer generates a VSTest-compatible adapter by default. Let me check the project files to provide more targeted guidance.","outputTokens":376,"requestId":"7035:32FCC3:481D08:54853D:69F2C32A"},"id":"9d7476a0-5f3b-40f9-b859-a817000bf072","timestamp":"2026-04-30T02:49:24.601Z","parentId":"91d7bc52-2aa1-4841-80f2-b0065a8be7a9"}
