{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"40adb8cc-f3cb-4c3f-9d1c-be7451c64791","content":"**The default test runner changed.** Starting with MSTest.Sdk **4.0**, the default runner switched from **VSTest** to **Microsoft.Testing.Platform**. Since `vstest.console` only works with the VSTest runner, it can no longer discover your tests.\n\nYou have two options:\n\n### Option 1 — Switch your CI to `dotnet test` (recommended)\nMicrosoft.Testing.Platform is the modern runner and `dotnet test` supports it natively. No project changes needed.\n\n### Option 2 — Opt back into VSTest\nAdd this to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n  <EnableMSTestRunner>false</EnableMSTestRunner>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nThis re-enables the classic VSTest adapter so `vstest.console` works again, but you lose the benefits of the new platform.\n\n**Recommendation:** Go with Option 1 — update your CI to use `dotnet test` instead of `vstest.console`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a2807946-5445-4627-b1e3-506599bd0780","outputTokens":259,"requestId":"702B:3BA9A2:45FD38:525E0A:69F2C334"},"id":"5caf9982-9582-44ce-a50c-06d02293522a","timestamp":"2026-04-30T02:49:31.057Z","parentId":"3f25e366-e56a-4b32-a6f7-db3423955ec9"}
